This paper is primarily focused on the privacy aspects of the shuffle model, which is a cryptographic protocol for ensuring privacy in data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and protocols for data analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy and communication complexity of the proposed protocol, which could place it in the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
